# Bundle Generate App Implementation Plan

This plan details the implementation of a new Django app (`bundle_generate`), a Merchant Database for storing products, a database seeding script, and an API endpoint to generate curated outfit bundles based on a selected merchant product using the existing compatibility engine.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Merchant Database Fields**: I will create a `MerchantProduct` model that closely mirrors `WardrobeItem` so it can seamlessly work with the `compatibility_engine`. Are there any specific merchant-only fields you want to add (e.g., `price`, `stock_url`, `merchant_name`)?
> - **User Context**: Should the `GenerateFromProductView` (the bundle generation API) also take a `user_id` to factor in user preferences (like avoided colors, favorite styles) when generating bundles from the merchant database?
> - **Category Mapping**: The prompt mentions "Topwear", "Bottomwear", and "Footwear". Internally, the engine uses "Top", "Bottom", and "Footwear" (from `Category` choices). I will map these automatically.

